values:
Alright so I haven't posted all semester, I guess it's time. Plus I need a study break.

To sum it up...
-Ryan and I are back together. And its more amazing than it was before. Don't ask me how it happened, but we've pretty much been inseparable since the very beginning of January. 
-We have a new kitty named Hugh Heffner in honor of our beer pong table...but that has slowly evolved into Hughbert and sometime Hubous. He's the fattest cat I've ever known. And if you fall asleep on our couch...watch out!
-I took a little sister in tibs, and it was a lot of fun! It made me enjoy it a lot more, I loved getting to know her and hang out more...but it was so much work and arts and crafts, something I'm definitely NOT good at.
-Somehow I've managed to survive the 18 hours I took. Got to go on tour with Philharmonia, which was really fun, and I got to hang out with a lot of people that I normally wouldn't hang out with.
-I'm officially in the College of Business, starting this summer in Finance. Graduation date unknown :)
-The Cruise of Drunken Dreams part II was so completely amazing. I'm ready for next year. Especially because I'll be 21...
-Speaking of which, mine and Casey's 21st was so much fun! We took a taxi out to the strip and got out and started running down Tennessee Street yelling "We're 21!!!!!!!" It was so fun. And ever since that it has been just as fun. Love it!
-Took lots of trips this year...Winter Haven, Atlanta, Charleston, Jacksonville, Sarasota, MEXICO, NEW ORLEANS, St. George Island, and soon to be Austin! :)

Those are the big things that have happened this semester. It's been fun. Now I'm just studying for finals and getting ready to go home for the first time all year!!! I have a lot of stuff planned, so I'm really excited. Alright...back to studying!

Ok, Austin it's been way too effing long. I finally went out and saw some live music downtown! OH MY GOSH I was in HEAVEN! We started the night off right by going to Hut's for some hamburgers, went to a local CD shop downtown, and then headed to Antone's to see Alejandro Escovedo. I had never heard him before, but I agreed to go just because I haven't seen any live band in years. Opening was Nathan Singleton and his Side Show Tragedy. I loooved them. You can even hear them on my myspace now :) I seriously could've just stayed there for days listening. Next was a band I wasn't too crazy about, but then Alejandro came out...it wasn't anything like I expected. He kinda looked like a classy Pedro from Napoleon Dynamite...but played rock and could really jam out...it was really cool. He played with an electric cello...that would take over the lead guitar sometimes. It was really cool. And he had lots of cool stories cuz he's been playing for foreverrrr. It was so fun...I really wanna start trying to go to shows in Tallahassee more. This is why I love Austin.

I'm home!!! Home is amazing and I love it. My flight home was probably the best I've ever had...even though I almost missed my flight in Atlanta cuz I was too busy playing on my laptop...oops! My flight got in early AND my bags were one of the first ones off. The next day we drove to Oklahoma...got some amazing Mexican food and I got to see my Uncle Greg!! My cousins looked so old...Ian didn't even know who I was cuz he wouldn't remember the last time he saw me. My grandparents were as slow as ever...I'm talkin we can't leave the house til 3pm because they can't get ready fast enough. It was definitely a different lifestyle for those 4 days...and made me realize that I'm going to be an active old person when I get old :) But it was still nice being with the fam. OH and I was DD for some of my fam when they went out to a bar...that was a lot of fun!! haha...Now I'm finalyl back at my real home...spent lots of quality time with my Andrew, many stories from that. Now for the sad news. We were driving around Austin today, and I was honestly completely LOST because we have 50 million new highways and toll roads and I had absolutely NO idea where we were. It's really sad to be lost in the city you grew up in. Really really sad. Everytime I come home they make another drastic change so I don't even recognize it...now there's all these new roads that I don't even know where they go to!!! But anyway. I'm babysitting for my neighbs tomorrow..it'll be nice to catch up with them...makin more Christmas cookies! Then Saturday it's off to Temple for my mom's family's Christmas...Sunday is Christmas Eve which means dinner at China Cafe, goin to see all the lights downtown..and possibly snow!?!? We'll see. And for the great news...I might get to go see the longhorns play in the Alamobowl on the 30th...crossing my fingers for tickets :) I've been running on the new trail (well...its new to me) in my neighborhood...it goes by the golf course and its really nice. Finished my Christmas shopping. Saw Stranger Than Fiction at the Alamo Drafthouse...it was really really good, I recommend it. Lovin seeing my doggies!! Belle is gettin old and gray...it's sad, but she's still my puppy. Ok so that's my week in a nutshell. Sorry its so random.

Life is a roller coaster...that about sums it up. Last week Bob lost it's baby kitty and bitchiest roommate and it was one of the hardest things we've all been through in a while...it was very traumatizing and so so sad. But it gets better every day...even though every little thing in this house reminds us of her...like our ghetto christmas tree...and opening up the front door and expecting her to come greet us and try to hug us like she always did...i dunno. I didn't know how much I loved that cat until she left us. Bob is definitely not the same.

But good news...I'm obsessed with my friends. Like no joke. I would so much rather be with friends than go out with a guy...which might be bad cuz I could be missing out on something really good...but I know my friends are never gonna break my heart and I don't wanna miss out on anything with them.

Bub is my new favorite word.


Home on Friday! Then it's off to Oklahoma to see my Uncle Greg and Aunt Cindy!!! I haven't seen them since before I graduated high school...and Greg is my faaaav! So I'm real excited about that. Then it's pretty much hangin out with the fam and Andrew for the next 2 weeks, then it's back to Tally for new year's with the regzzzzzzzz. My heart really does belong to the regz. Love it.


later bubs
Rest in peace little kitty...you were a bitch but we wouldn't have had it any other way! We'll miss you.

Just wanna say that there is an animal running round in the attic (if we even have one) but whatever it is, it sounds bigger than a rat and it has big claws. Aff called the landlord but I think it's too late today...speaking of the landlord, I called him when I was drunk the other night. I found that amusing!

IT'S OVER!!! My recitals are over...my junior recital..the one I was worried about...I couldn't have asked it to go any better, and it was even more amazing cuz all of my best friends were there and it made me feel really good :) After listening to the recording...mistakes I made were not noticeable...so I'm relaly happy. The even better news...I think it may have (knock on wood) gotten rid of my nerves. Tonight for the second recital, I went to play and I was really not that nervous at all. I didn't play as well, because it had not been my focus at all, but it was a great performance just in that I was nervous at all...it was the weirdest feeling. 

My mom left this morning, it was sad, but I'll be home in about a month, and I can't freakin wait! My life just got a whole lot easier today, I don't really have any worries except for keepin my grades up now. LOVE IT!

In other news...Jeff Bowden resigned today...Meghan called and told me but when she told me I heard "Jeff Bowden died today!" i was like what!?!?!? Anywayyyyyyyy

Thanksgiving is soon!! I'm stayin in Tally with Jim and Chuck and we will have our own little feast. 

That's it bye!

My mom is amazing. I'm so so so happy she's here, even if it is for only 2 days. When spent the day shopping, talking, laughing and gossiping about everything in Texas. She told me she wanted to take me to Osaka...and I didn't complain! She's the person I can count on for absolutely anything, and she's pretty much amazing. 

Tomorrow is the recital. So ready to get it over with!!! I played Lookout for my mom today..she was kinda shocked...it was funny :)

The Cruise of Drunken Dreams part II is officially booked for spring break 07! 

Me and Case talk about our 21st birthday pretty much every day. We are lame.

Both my teams broke my heart yesterday...at least Texas had an excuse. Colt got hurt the first drive of the game. We had 2 perfectly functioning QBs, but no. We had fun in the stands though...I pretty much went crazy after being soaked and cold for 3 hours...so it was fun!

I'm too full to function.

I've been kinda frustrated the past few weeks. And just need to vent a little. Lately we've made lots of random plans here and there...and so many times people just dont follow through. Like earlier last week the boys watned to have a bonfire but then ditch us last minute. And it's been happening so much lately that everytime we talk about doing something, I doubt that it will even go through, just so I don't get my hopes up. It's one of my biggest peeves in the world...and I know I'm guilty of it every now and then, but I really try to if I make plans to follow through, because I know it sucks being on the other end every time. And white lies to cover it up don't make it any better. Anywaysssssssss......

But that's all! Time to go to a recital...only like 4 more. !!

Our house is the most ghetto thing ever. I swear, every single day it's something new! Let me make a list of things that give our house "character" as we so lovingly put it....

-first, the dryer vent got unplugged so all the heat would just go straight into the bathroom
-both toilets are messed up so you can't use the flusher, you have pull the thing up to flush
-steph and case's shower shocks them everytime they turn a knob
-their bathroom and steph's room both don't have knobs for the doors
-there is a new smell everytime we walk in
-the plug that the microwave was in doesn't work, and we can't find the circuit breaker in our house
-the part on the ac that displays the temperature got ripped off
-the cat got stuck in the dryer today cuz she crawls through the vent
-THEN a possum got stuck........thank you neighbors!!!

i could go on and on! but somehow we have come to love all the things wrong with our house...and look forward to finding out what will be wrong every new day!


other than all that mess...here's some random info
-we had a bonfire last night, it was funnn
-jon mayer came to visit us this weekend, there are endless stories about that one!
-jury on monday, time to freak out. my pianist is just not clicking with me
-recital in less than 3 weeks, but my mom is comin!
-school is taking over. blahhhhh

I'm on cloud 9 right now for no apparent reason. I'm so happy with life right now...school is going really really well, I'm managing my time, preparing for my recital which is coming along better than I thought. I'm actually enjoying practicing and I want to practice for once in my life. And it's weird...I still don't really want to make a career out of music, but I'm just enjoying it for once and doing it for me. Which is the way it should have been all along.

Looking back a year ago, my life was completely different. I lived in a different place, I only had one major and a different life plan, I had a boyfriend...and now all of those things are the exact opposite. But I'm so happy. I am constantly surrounded by the most amazing friends...words cant even express how amazing they are. I'm keeping myself in good shape...I start almost every day with a run, and it makes my days so much better...even if I'm tired it wakes me up and gets the endorphins going. I am happy being single for once...I thought about it, and at this point in my life I don't want a guy...I love being able to go out and have fun and not worry about asking if it's okay to go out and do those things. I'm just happy and I love it!

This weekend was completely amazing. Friday was a cookout at Betty and then Harry. We sat out in lawn chairs all afternoon drinkin beer...I made my queso..and well after that is up for you to decide! Saturday morning we woke up and I drove Steph over to Betty so she could get her car...where we talked about everything that had happened the night before. LOVE IT! We had so much fun that we decided to do it all over again on Saturday. Except this time my queso broke their microwave. oops! We then went to the pub where Steph and I somehow were banded as 21, and we ran into the guys I have a crush on and talked to them the whole night :) It was a blast and it was so nice to wake up and not have to worry about a football game taking up the entire day.

More exciting news:
-my junior recital is on nov. 13th and my mom just booked a flight to come and see it!!!!!!!!!!
-my parents came to visit 2 weekends ago and that was so fun. I love my family so so so much and I feel so lucky to have family like them.
-Halloween Horror nights this weekend along with a trip to Gainsville.
-I had 3 tests this past week and made A's on all of them!!
-I made my CD for the competition and it turned out really good I think.
-Nip/Tuck is so good.

and something completely random: that petsmart commercial with the dachshund and her stuffed animal makes me wanna cry every time!!!!

and finally....life is picking up so fast i don't even know what to do with myself. I feel like there's so much I need to do in the next month and I have no idea how I'll do it all...but I somehow always seem to find a way.

So the fam came this weekend, that was a lot of fun :) I love when my family comes to visit...and they get to see how my life is here and they actually get to be a part of it for once! It was just too short of a trip, and now I won't see them again til Christmas..but hey, I've gone longer I guess.

There's a new dent in my car...that's hit #3 with no note! Thanks people.

I got my Ipod back!!!! yesss

3 off weekends in a row. Thank the lord. I need it real bad. It's wearing me out, and the first thing that I slack off on is school, and that needs to change.

Short update...bedtime!

life is full of unecessary drama!

my parents got into an accident this weekend that totaled their car...everyones ok, but pretty shaken up about it still :( and it was on the way to church!

life just got more stressful today when i found out i have an audition tape due on october 1st first that i had no idea was due that soon. yikes.

section leader is fun but i feel like people are constantly judging and thinking they can do it better than me. thats the not fun part.

this year is gonna be fun.

Ok so i think this fall is going to be great. My classes dont start til at least 11:15, so I'm gonna be waking up early and doing things like homework, running, and working out in the morning so I can have my evenings free and its going to be amazing! My audition went really well today...chiefs is going well (even if some people dont think I'm good at my job, i'm having fun doing it) and my friends are still just as amazing. I love my house because at any given moment theres always people comin over to visit.

The only bad thing: I woke up with a roach on me last night. GROSS!!!!!!!!!!!! Needless to say I'm a little scared to go to sleep tonight. :(

But yeah, life is good besides a few things...like people screwing with my head, but I'm getting over it, and moving on.

Oh, and my mom says I'm going to meet my new boy in my business calc class...lets cross our fingers.

Sooo I made it home smoothly for the first time in how long???? School is over, even though it doesn't feel like it, it just feels like the weekend and in 2 days (or when I get back to Tally) I'll be goin back. I've had a blastttt so far, and tomorrow we leave for corpus for a weekend at the beach and dog races :) Then its quality time with my Andrew and the few friends I'll get to see before I leave again on Tuesday. 

Let's see.....
-I think I pulled off A's at TCC which makes me happy.
-Orlando was a blast
-Me and Jimmy have a furniture moving company to help out those in need
-Chiefs in freakin less than a week
-I did a ton of shopping today. Found a gorgeousss dress and accessories :)
-My family is pretty amazing, not gonna lie.
-Apparently you can't bring liquids into airports anymore.
-My hair is even blodner and i love it.
-I gotta get up at 8 in them orning tomorrow. yuck
-I like lists like these cuz I can be random
-I'm texting my friend Mike right now that I've had a crush on since 8th grade and we might hang out!
-I'm sick of school...2 years straight and summer school for the rest of my life is going to kill me.
-I love big brother and days of our lives
-It's going to be so so weird when everyone gets back. We all have our inside jokes and our dumb things that no one else is ever going to get. But i can't wait.
-Linda Snyder=Linda Synder, Jihnda, Jaich, Jinja Ninja, Ginger, Lindy...etc etc
-I'm done.

When things are going great someone just has to come along and ruin it for me. insert every possible curse word here....

I can do this.

-We saw Superman last night and it was amazingggggggg. I'm in love! Can I please be Lois Lane?
-June 26th: a night to remember with the fab 4 :) love it.
-TCC is unbelievably easy right now...I wish I could be sleeping instead of going to classes
-Work is okay. I don't like it as much as Chili's...they schedule too many people everyday and therefore I don't make as much money. It also exhausts me.
-I'm gettin back into my gym schedule! love it.
-Today I called my mom and they are on their trip to Iowa to see my favorite aunt and uncle...that i haven't seen in almost 2 1/2 years now :( I don't think my little cousin would even know who I am! They are in Oklahoma right now seeing the rest of my family that I don't know when I'll ever see again...that's what sucks about being so far from home!!
-I love being in love and having that one person that cares about you more than anything...I want it back so so bad!
-The teeth came out...it was a long week of hangin out not being able to do much, but I'm pretty much back to normal and very happy about that :)
-I want Meghan and Steph to come back!
-I asked off work for 4th of July + No school = fun.
-I want to take a road trip in the next couple weeks!
-And that's it for now.

WHY CANT I JUST FLY HOME AND HAVE EVERYTHING RUN SMOOTHLY?!?!

The flight to Houston was fine (well I found out later that it didn't really). I had a 2 hour layover there, and then we load the plane and everything is fine. We leave the gate....THREE hours later we are in the air. We sat on the runway because of rain...it was awful. And the whole time my parents are waiting at the airport in Austin and have no idea why or when I'll be there. So I finalyyyy get to Austin and get to the baggage claim to get my bag. Oh wait...my bag wasn't there. On the screen it said "last bag on" so that meant my bag did not make it to Austin. Andddd I had left my baggage claim ticket on the plane. AWESOME! The lady wasn't much help...gave us a number to call later to see if they find it. We call about 2 hours later...the lady on the phone was a lot more helpful...somehow even though I was on Continental, my bag made it onto a Delta flight, so it got delivered to my house much, much later that night. My neighbor is a pilot for Continental and has never heard of that happening before. I HATE FLYING!!!

But on a happier note, I got to see Andrew...and his gf Alicia yesterday, and she was nice to me this time. I miss him so much and wish he was aroudn more. Today we went to Six Flags and that was a blast. Tonight we went to get Mexican food with the fam, my parents were gettin drunk and that was also a blast, hah! And now I'm just hangin out...I'll be up in 7 hours to get my teeth out, hooray! So that's my visit so far, don't be jeal :)

-Saw the omen tonight, bigggg disappointment
-Summer has been fun and very chill.
-We make it a point to go to a pool/beach/spring almost every day it seems like
-Meghan visits soon!!!!!!!!!!
-Me and case are on a mission...and it's gonna work dammit!
-I'm so glad I'm taking these stupid classes in 6 weeks instead of a full semester
-Got a job at Fridays, but I guess they like to train people and then just not schedule them...oh well!
-Quit Abercrombie by not going. I pulled an Office Space :)
-Home in 2 weeks for wisdom teeth...should be fun! I'll get some Six Flags and Andrew on the side though :)
-My friends are freakin amazing, you guys have helped me sooo much lately, I don't think you even know.
-I love Steph and Case's new cat ______.
-I eat out wayyyyy too much.
-I'm missing out on a cruise thanks to freakin summer school.
-If Friday's doesn't cooperate I have the opportunity to do modeling which I would love to try.
-this house is veryyyyy lonely. I'm not here much.
-KDOG came to visit this weekend! I miss everyone that left this summer :(
-ummmmm that's all I can think of.
-I love my friends.

First of all, let me just say that I'm very glad I'm not living in the Backyard next year. Too many break ins and cop chases for my taste! Second of all for some reason one of my biggest pet peaves is a dirty kitchen and people who don't put away their dishes! It's not hard!!!!!! Everytime I see a dish in the sink that's not mine I think...I'm not gonna put it away, I'm gonna wait for whoever do it to do it....but no that never happens and I just get more angry looking at it everytimme I walk into the kitchen. It sounds dumb, I know, but it drives me CRAZY!!!!

Now that I got that off my chest! I had my last 9am studio class today!!!!!!!! Only 2 days of classes left. In one week I'll be done with everything school related. Monday I have theory, sight singing and dynamic earth exams (and also ryan's bday!). Tuesday is my jury. Wednesday is Music Tech. Then I'm DONE!!!! And then I get to go home!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

I can't freakin wait for this weekend!! It'll be lots of relaxing, orientation with On The Border, a day trip to the beach for our 6 month anniversary...and maybe a little drinkin in there somewhere! It'll be the break I need for the last 2 weeks of school and then its time to go home FINALLY! I'll get a much needed break from this town and go to the greatest city ever. Then it's back for summer school and lots of work at 2 jobs. 

We've been hangin out with Marna, Stephanie, and Ashley a lot lately and I looove them! Marna has been my partner in crime lately lol. check plus.

School is so close to being out...but it seems like its never gonna get here. I still have tonsss to do. Yikes.

So Ryan told his mom before she ever came into town that he wanted to spend today (my bday) with me. Now she's not sure if she's gonna let him come to dinner tonight. I'm a little upset about that. And last night frustrated me to no end. But whatevvvvvv

This weekend has been amazing. It proved to me that I don't need my boyfriend to have fun, he doesn't have to go everywhere I go...and it was so fun. Friday night was gonna be low key, but I was talkin to Marna online and she was like me and Stephanie (Riesdorph) are goin to a party and invited me to come. I said sure!! So I tried calling other Stephanie cuz she wanted to do something and she didn't answer so Marna said that we should go to her house and make her go! Steph was asleep, we woke her up and told her to put on clothes and come...and we convinced Aff to go too. Needless to say...we had a blast. We didn't know anyone there, so I'm sure we pissed a few people off, I know Aff pissed one girl off lol, and I tried convincing everyone my name was Stephanie too. 

Yesterday was a blast too. I woke up and Julez called me to go to Backyard Burgers, then we went to Bob to hang out until the Garnet and Gold game. It was lots of fun, didn't pay much attention to the actual game. We got new drum majors, congrats to them! Then I went home and took a nap with Tank :) I'm dogsitting for Ryan and I have become slightly attached to this dog! Then I had to go to the USO concert, and then it was out for Ashley's bday party! The cops came, so we moved it to Betty...then the SAME cops came and busted that party too. It was a lot of fun though. We made green beans and apparently I put too much garlic in them...oops.

So I don't know if this would piss anyone else off, or if I'm being too sensitive, but it really hurt my feelings. Ryan forgot his cell phone charger in Tallahassee. So the only way we could talk was if he was home at his house. He was going to a party, and told me he would call me at "9:59" and then if i didn't answer he'd call me at 10, then again at 10:30. Now I'm not an idiot. I know how easy it is to ask someone at a party if you can borrow their phone, especially if everyone there are your best friends from high school. At 4am he calls me from his house. I didn't answer cuz it would've been a bad idea. And then he IMs me saying he tried so hard to call me but he just couldn't. It hurts my feelings because he nows I'm already worried cuz his ex is gonna be there, and he doesn't even try to call me from the party. I'm freakin babysitting his dog, I've done everything for this dog and he wont give me the time of day cuz he's at a party. Whatever, sorry just had to vent.

School is getting quite hectic...but today it hit me that the end is sooo close and it will come by so fast. I'm getting soo homesick again and it doesn't help that my parents have been tellin me about all the stuff they wanna do when I get back...hiking, going to the cabin on the river, lots and family and eating, and of course I gotta see my friends!! I'm so so excited.

I've also become very lazy with school. I practice the complete bare minimum to get me by. I'm doing the bare minimum and somehow I'm doing better than when I cared with school! I decided yesterday that I'm gonna do the double major instead. I'll be here longer, but I'm really in no rush. And yesterday in the union I got offered a job at Abercrombie! I only have to work 1 shift once every other week or so, so I can still get another job, but also have the discount :) I'm looking forward to summer. Money...taking classes, but one I'm takin with Steph and the others are going to be fun cuz its for my new major!

I'm really proud of myself, cuz even after the cruise I've been really good about going to the gym. It's not what I should be doing with my free time, but it's my stress relief, and I need that pretty much every day. So it's completely worth it.

And that's all I got!!

Alright so I haven't updated in a while. Spring break was absolutely amazing...I would write about it but it would probly depress me too much...so I'll just say Daytona was fun and the cruise was even more fun :)

St. Patty's day was fun...i think lol! Me and Steph got pushed on stage at Floyd's...I can't really say I remember it. I think that's the most drunk I've been in forevvvvv. But it was a good time. Then the next day we had a BBQ for Nikki's b-day!

We saw V for Vendetta and it was sooo good. And that night made me realize how lucky I am to have a guy like Ryan. On the way home we were laughing so hard we couldn't breathe, thinking the exact same things at the same time (it was weird, trust me...and we do it all the time) and then later that night we laughed even harder while we attempted to give his english bulldog a bath lol.

Life is good...my friends are amazing. Even though I still hate my major, there's too many other good things to let that get me down!
So it's either keep my major and hate it or change my major and go back home. It seems like I lose either way...

Life is getting better these days. I've been going to abs and back 3 or 4 times a week, and I'm gonna start running (!!!!!!) again tomorrow. I feel so much better when I work out. Today is a rainy day and I just want to sleep all day...but nope I won't be done for like 4 1/2 more hours :( Things with Ryan are completely amazing...I can't even put into words how great he is. I love him so much. We go to bed every night with every intention of falling asleep early but then we end up goofing off all night long. Like we always say...cheers to never breaking up.

Tonight is gonna be GIRLS NIGHT! at Floyd's. I'm pretty stoked!

Alright here's a few random updates...

-I'm pretty sure I'm addicted to Taco Bell.
-After about 150 bucks...my laptop is fixed.
-Mom sent me girl scout cookies today!!
-I'm still confused as ever about my major.
-I had a really good time in Orlando, suprisingly, and I realized a lot of people in the studio are really really cool.
-Foreign people are fun to impersonate.
-I surprised Ryan on my way home from Orlando, and got him good.
-I found out I'm going to get reimbursed for gas.
-Sophomore recital: February 21st at 8pm. Mark your calendars.
-I cleaned my room and made it cute today!
-I'm missing my Andrew like CRAZY. He's the one person that knows me better than myself...and I've needed him so bad this semester.
-Been going to the gym a lot...gotta get that Bahama Body :)
-I'm incredibly stressed about everything I have to do this semester.
-I left my charger in orlando. Ouch.
-Bachelor night tonight!
-I'm pretty sure my theory and ss/et teacher hates me.
-And I can't think of anything else.

I have had a really bad first 2 weeks of school. I figured out that I probly want to change my major, but then I will lose my out of state waiver and the past 2 years of school would pretty much be a waste. It's stressing me out beyond belief. My laptop is completely broken and that's been most of my stress lately because no matter what I try it wont get fixed and I've been computerless for a while. My dad had me send my computer home which costed 75 dollars!!! so he could look at it. Plus my dad already spent 20 bucks to get my installation cd here and that didn't even work. My professor is pissed at me, which is always fun. Butttt I also have great news. The cruise for spring break is officially booked!!! The cruise of drunken dreams will set sail on March 6th, but after we spend the weekend at Kali's condo in Daytona! Spring break is going to be completely amazing...everytime I think about it I get soooo excited. Another good thing is me and Ryan have been together for 3 months now, and I'm soo happy with him. I guess I'll be really really late and talk about the orange bowl...it was sooo fun. We stayed on the beach, and had so much fun (besides all the pointless things we had to do lol). We had an adventure the first night where we went on the service elevator into the kitchen and stole stickers, then got in trouble with the guy at the front desk. It was hilarious.
